Note:
Runa Standard Library: Priority Queue Implementation

Provides comprehensive priority queue functionality using heap-based data structures for efficient 
priority-based operations. Supports both min and max heap operations with custom priority handling 
and advanced queue management features.

Production-grade features include:
- Binary heap implementation with O(log n) operations
- Min-heap and max-heap priority queues
- Priority-based task scheduling and event management  
- Bulk operations and batch processing
- Queue statistics and performance monitoring
- Full Dictionary-based implementation for Runa compliance
:End Note

Note: Core Priority Queue Type Definition
Type PriorityQueue is Dictionary with:
    items as List[Dictionary]
    size as Integer
    heap_type as String
    comparisons_count as Integer
    insertions_count as Integer
    extractions_count as Integer

Note: Priority Queue Node Creation
Process called "create_priority_node" that takes value as Any and priority as Float returns Dictionary:
    Let timestamp be get_current_timestamp()
    Return dictionary with:
        value as value
        priority as priority
        timestamp as timestamp
        insertion_order as 0

Process called "create_priority_queue" that returns Dictionary:
    Return dictionary with:
        items as list containing
        size as 0
        heap_type as "min"
        comparisons_count as 0
        insertions_count as 0
        extractions_count as 0

Process called "create_min_priority_queue" that returns Dictionary:
    Let pq be create_priority_queue()
    Set pq["heap_type"] to "min"
    Return pq

Process called "create_max_priority_queue" that returns Dictionary:
    Let pq be create_priority_queue()
    Set pq["heap_type"] to "max"
    Return pq

Note: Heap Navigation Functions
Process called "get_parent_index" that takes index as Integer returns Integer:
    If index is less than or equal to 0:
        Return -1
    Return (index minus 1) divided by 2

Process called "get_left_child_index" that takes index as Integer returns Integer:
    Return (2 multiplied by index) plus 1

Process called "get_right_child_index" that takes index as Integer returns Integer:
    Return (2 multiplied by index) plus 2

Process called "has_parent" that takes index as Integer returns Boolean:
    Return get_parent_index with index as index is greater than or equal to 0

Process called "has_left_child" that takes pq as Dictionary and index as Integer returns Boolean:
    Return get_left_child_index with index as index is less than pq["size"]

Process called "has_right_child" that takes pq as Dictionary and index as Integer returns Boolean:
    Return get_right_child_index with index as index is less than pq["size"]

Process called "get_parent_node" that takes pq as Dictionary and index as Integer returns Dictionary:
    Let parent_index be get_parent_index with index as index
    Return pq["items"][parent_index]

Process called "get_left_child_node" that takes pq as Dictionary and index as Integer returns Dictionary:
    Let left_index be get_left_child_index with index as index
    Return pq["items"][left_index]

Process called "get_right_child_node" that takes pq as Dictionary and index as Integer returns Dictionary:
    Let right_index be get_right_child_index with index as index
    Return pq["items"][right_index]

Note: Priority Comparison Functions
Process called "should_swap_with_parent" that takes pq as Dictionary and child_index as Integer returns Boolean:
    If not has_parent with index as child_index:
        Return false
    
    Let child_node be pq["items"][child_index]
    Let parent_node be get_parent_node with pq as pq and index as child_index
    
    Set pq["comparisons_count"] to pq["comparisons_count"] plus 1
    
    If pq["heap_type"] is equal to "min":
        If child_node["priority"] is less than parent_node["priority"]:
            Return true
        If child_node["priority"] is equal to parent_node["priority"]:
            Return child_node["timestamp"] is less than parent_node["timestamp"]
        Return false
    Otherwise:
        If child_node["priority"] is greater than parent_node["priority"]:
            Return true
        If child_node["priority"] is equal to parent_node["priority"]:
            Return child_node["timestamp"] is less than parent_node["timestamp"]
        Return false

Process called "get_priority_child_index" that takes pq as Dictionary and parent_index as Integer returns Integer:
    If not has_left_child with pq as pq and index as parent_index:
        Return -1
    
    Let left_index be get_left_child_index with index as parent_index
    Let priority_index be left_index
    
    If has_right_child with pq as pq and index as parent_index:
        Let right_index be get_right_child_index with index as parent_index
        Let left_node be pq["items"][left_index]
        Let right_node be pq["items"][right_index]
        
        Set pq["comparisons_count"] to pq["comparisons_count"] plus 1
        
        If pq["heap_type"] is equal to "min":
            If right_node["priority"] is less than left_node["priority"]:
                Set priority_index to right_index
            Otherwise if right_node["priority"] is equal to left_node["priority"]:
                If right_node["timestamp"] is less than left_node["timestamp"]:
                    Set priority_index to right_index
        Otherwise:
            If right_node["priority"] is greater than left_node["priority"]:
                Set priority_index to right_index
            Otherwise if right_node["priority"] is equal to left_node["priority"]:
                If right_node["timestamp"] is less than left_node["timestamp"]:
                    Set priority_index to right_index
    
    Return priority_index

Process called "should_swap_with_child" that takes pq as Dictionary and parent_index as Integer returns Boolean:
    Let child_index be get_priority_child_index with pq as pq and parent_index as parent_index
    If child_index is equal to -1:
        Return false
    
    Let parent_node be pq["items"][parent_index]
    Let child_node be pq["items"][child_index]
    
    Set pq["comparisons_count"] to pq["comparisons_count"] plus 1
    
    If pq["heap_type"] is equal to "min":
        If child_node["priority"] is less than parent_node["priority"]:
            Return true
        If child_node["priority"] is equal to parent_node["priority"]:
            Return child_node["timestamp"] is less than parent_node["timestamp"]
        Return false
    Otherwise:
        If child_node["priority"] is greater than parent_node["priority"]:
            Return true
        If child_node["priority"] is equal to parent_node["priority"]:
            Return child_node["timestamp"] is less than parent_node["timestamp"]
        Return false

Note: Heap Manipulation Functions
Process called "swap_nodes" that takes pq as Dictionary and index1 as Integer and index2 as Integer returns Dictionary:
    Let temp be pq["items"][index1]
    Set pq["items"][index1] to pq["items"][index2]
    Set pq["items"][index2] to temp
    Return pq

Process called "heapify_up" that takes pq as Dictionary and index as Integer returns Dictionary:
    Let current_index be index
    While should_swap_with_parent with pq as pq and child_index as current_index:
        Let parent_index be get_parent_index with index as current_index
        Set pq to swap_nodes with pq as pq and index1 as current_index and index2 as parent_index
        Set current_index to parent_index
    Return pq

Process called "heapify_down" that takes pq as Dictionary and index as Integer returns Dictionary:
    Let current_index be index
    While should_swap_with_child with pq as pq and parent_index as current_index:
        Let child_index be get_priority_child_index with pq as pq and parent_index as current_index
        Set pq to swap_nodes with pq as pq and index1 as current_index and index2 as child_index
        Set current_index to child_index
    Return pq

Note: Core Priority Queue Operations
Process called "priority_queue_push" that takes pq as Dictionary and value as Any and priority as Float returns Dictionary:
    Let node be create_priority_node with value as value and priority as priority
    Set node["insertion_order"] to pq["insertions_count"]
    
    Add node to pq["items"]
    Set pq["size"] to pq["size"] plus 1
    Set pq["insertions_count"] to pq["insertions_count"] plus 1
    
    Set pq to heapify_up with pq as pq and index as pq["size"] minus 1
    Return pq

Process called "priority_queue_peek" that takes pq as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    If pq["size"] is equal to 0:
        Return dictionary with:
            success as false
            value as None
            priority as 0.0
            error_message as "Priority queue is empty"
    
    Let top_node be pq["items"][0]
    Return dictionary with:
        success as true
        value as top_node["value"]
        priority as top_node["priority"]
        timestamp as top_node["timestamp"]

Process called "priority_queue_pop" that takes pq as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    If pq["size"] is equal to 0:
        Return dictionary with:
            success as false
            value as None
            priority as 0.0
            queue as pq
            error_message as "Priority queue is empty"
    
    Let top_node be pq["items"][0]
    Let result_value be top_node["value"]
    Let result_priority be top_node["priority"]
    
    Set pq["items"][0] to pq["items"][pq["size"] minus 1]
    Remove last element from pq["items"]
    Set pq["size"] to pq["size"] minus 1
    Set pq["extractions_count"] to pq["extractions_count"] plus 1
    
    If pq["size"] is greater than 0:
        Set pq to heapify_down with pq as pq and index as 0
    
    Return dictionary with:
        success as true
        value as result_value
        priority as result_priority
        queue as pq

Process called "priority_queue_push_multiple" that takes pq as Dictionary and items as List[Dictionary] returns Dictionary:
    For each item in items:
        Let value be item["value"]
        Let priority be item["priority"]
        Set pq to priority_queue_push with pq as pq and value as value and priority as priority
    Return pq

Process called "priority_queue_pop_multiple" that takes pq as Dictionary and count as Integer returns Dictionary:
    Let results be list containing
    Let updated_pq be pq
    Let items_popped be 0
    
    While items_popped is less than count and updated_pq["size"] is greater than 0:
        Let pop_result be priority_queue_pop with pq as updated_pq
        If pop_result["success"]:
            Add dictionary with:
                value as pop_result["value"]
                priority as pop_result["priority"]
            to results
            Set updated_pq to pop_result["queue"]
            Set items_popped to items_popped plus 1
        Otherwise:
            Break
    
    Return dictionary with:
        success as true
        items as results
        items_popped as items_popped
        queue as updated_pq

Note: Query and Analysis Functions
Process called "priority_queue_is_empty" that takes pq as Dictionary returns Boolean:
    Return pq["size"] is equal to 0

Process called "priority_queue_size" that takes pq as Dictionary returns Integer:
    Return pq["size"]

Process called "priority_queue_contains_value" that takes pq as Dictionary and target_value as Any returns Boolean:
    For each node in pq["items"]:
        If node["value"] is equal to target_value:
            Return true
    Return false

Process called "priority_queue_contains_priority" that takes pq as Dictionary and target_priority as Float returns Boolean:
    For each node in pq["items"]:
        If node["priority"] is equal to target_priority:
            Return true
    Return false

Process called "priority_queue_get_all_values" that takes pq as Dictionary returns List[Any]:
    Let values be list containing
    For each node in pq["items"]:
        Add node["value"] to values
    Return values

Process called "priority_queue_get_all_priorities" that takes pq as Dictionary returns List[Float]:
    Let priorities be list containing
    For each node in pq["items"]:
        Add node["priority"] to priorities
    Return priorities

Process called "priority_queue_find_by_value" that takes pq as Dictionary and target_value as Any returns Dictionary:
    For i from 0 to pq["size"] minus 1:
        Let node be pq["items"][i]
        If node["value"] is equal to target_value:
            Return dictionary with:
                found as true
                index as i
                value as node["value"]
                priority as node["priority"]
                timestamp as node["timestamp"]
    
    Return dictionary with:
        found as false
        index as -1
        value as None
        priority as 0.0

Note: Advanced Priority Queue Operations
Process called "priority_queue_update_priority" that takes pq as Dictionary and target_value as Any and new_priority as Float returns Dictionary:
    Let find_result be priority_queue_find_by_value with pq as pq and target_value as target_value
    If not find_result["found"]:
        Return dictionary with:
            success as false
            queue as pq
            error_message as "Value not found in priority queue"
    
    Let index be find_result["index"]
    Let old_priority be pq["items"][index]["priority"]
    Set pq["items"][index]["priority"] to new_priority
    Set pq["items"][index]["timestamp"] to get_current_timestamp()
    
    If new_priority is less than old_priority and pq["heap_type"] is equal to "min":
        Set pq to heapify_up with pq as pq and index as index
    Otherwise if new_priority is greater than old_priority and pq["heap_type"] is equal to "max":
        Set pq to heapify_up with pq as pq and index as index
    Otherwise:
        Set pq to heapify_down with pq as pq and index as index
    
    Return dictionary with:
        success as true
        queue as pq
        old_priority as old_priority
        new_priority as new_priority

Process called "priority_queue_remove_value" that takes pq as Dictionary and target_value as Any returns Dictionary:
    Let find_result be priority_queue_find_by_value with pq as pq and target_value as target_value
    If not find_result["found"]:
        Return dictionary with:
            success as false
            queue as pq
            error_message as "Value not found in priority queue"
    
    Let index be find_result["index"]
    Let removed_priority be pq["items"][index]["priority"]
    
    Set pq["items"][index] to pq["items"][pq["size"] minus 1]
    Remove last element from pq["items"]
    Set pq["size"] to pq["size"] minus 1
    
    If pq["size"] is greater than 0 and index is less than pq["size"]:
        Let parent_index be get_parent_index with index as index
        If parent_index is greater than or equal to 0 and should_swap_with_parent with pq as pq and child_index as index:
            Set pq to heapify_up with pq as pq and index as index
        Otherwise:
            Set pq to heapify_down with pq as pq and index as index
    
    Return dictionary with:
        success as true
        queue as pq
        removed_value as target_value
        removed_priority as removed_priority

Process called "priority_queue_clear" that takes pq as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Set pq["items"] to list containing
    Set pq["size"] to 0
    Set pq["comparisons_count"] to 0
    Set pq["insertions_count"] to 0
    Set pq["extractions_count"] to 0
    Return pq

Process called "priority_queue_copy" that takes pq as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Let new_pq be create_priority_queue()
    Set new_pq["heap_type"] to pq["heap_type"]
    Set new_pq["comparisons_count"] to pq["comparisons_count"]
    Set new_pq["insertions_count"] to pq["insertions_count"]
    Set new_pq["extractions_count"] to pq["extractions_count"]
    
    For each node in pq["items"]:
        Let new_node be dictionary with:
            value as node["value"]
            priority as node["priority"]
            timestamp as node["timestamp"]
            insertion_order as node["insertion_order"]
        Add new_node to new_pq["items"]
    
    Set new_pq["size"] to pq["size"]
    Return new_pq

Note: Heap Validation and Utility Functions
Process called "priority_queue_is_valid_heap" that takes pq as Dictionary returns Boolean:
    For i from 0 to pq["size"] minus 1:
        If has_left_child with pq as pq and index as i:
            Let left_index be get_left_child_index with index as i
            If should_swap_with_child with pq as pq and parent_index as i:
                Return false
        
        If has_right_child with pq as pq and index as i:
            Let right_index be get_right_child_index with index as i
            If should_swap_with_child with pq as pq and parent_index as i:
                Return false
    
    Return true

Process called "priority_queue_get_height" that takes pq as Dictionary returns Integer:
    If pq["size"] is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    
    Let height be 0
    Let level_size be 1
    Let remaining_nodes be pq["size"]
    
    While remaining_nodes is greater than 0:
        Set height to height plus 1
        Set remaining_nodes to remaining_nodes minus level_size
        Set level_size to level_size multiplied by 2
    
    Return height

Process called "priority_queue_statistics" that takes pq as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    If pq["size"] is equal to 0:
        Return dictionary with:
            size as 0
            height as 0
            heap_type as pq["heap_type"]
            is_valid as true
            comparisons_count as pq["comparisons_count"]
            insertions_count as pq["insertions_count"]
            extractions_count as pq["extractions_count"]
            average_priority as 0.0
            priority_range as 0.0
    
    Let total_priority be 0.0
    Let min_priority be pq["items"][0]["priority"]
    Let max_priority be pq["items"][0]["priority"]
    
    For each node in pq["items"]:
        Set total_priority to total_priority plus node["priority"]
        If node["priority"] is less than min_priority:
            Set min_priority to node["priority"]
        If node["priority"] is greater than max_priority:
            Set max_priority to node["priority"]
    
    Return dictionary with:
        size as pq["size"]
        height as priority_queue_get_height with pq as pq
        heap_type as pq["heap_type"]
        is_valid as priority_queue_is_valid_heap with pq as pq
        comparisons_count as pq["comparisons_count"]
        insertions_count as pq["insertions_count"]
        extractions_count as pq["extractions_count"]
        average_priority as total_priority divided by pq["size"] as Float
        min_priority as min_priority
        max_priority as max_priority
        priority_range as max_priority minus min_priority

Note: Specialized Priority Queue Operations
Process called "priority_queue_merge" that takes pq1 as Dictionary and pq2 as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    If pq1["heap_type"] is not equal to pq2["heap_type"]:
        Return dictionary with:
            success as false
            queue as pq1
            error_message as "Cannot merge heaps of different types"
    
    Let merged_pq be priority_queue_copy with pq as pq1
    
    For each node in pq2["items"]:
        Set merged_pq to priority_queue_push with pq as merged_pq and value as node["value"] and priority as node["priority"]
    
    Return dictionary with:
        success as true
        queue as merged_pq

Process called "priority_queue_to_sorted_list" that takes pq as Dictionary returns List[Dictionary]:
    Let temp_pq be priority_queue_copy with pq as pq
    Let sorted_items be list containing
    
    While temp_pq["size"] is greater than 0:
        Let pop_result be priority_queue_pop with pq as temp_pq
        If pop_result["success"]:
            Add dictionary with:
                value as pop_result["value"]
                priority as pop_result["priority"]
            to sorted_items
            Set temp_pq to pop_result["queue"]
        Otherwise:
            Break
    
    Return sorted_items

Process called "priority_queue_peek_multiple" that takes pq as Dictionary and count as Integer returns List[Dictionary]:
    Let temp_pq be priority_queue_copy with pq as pq
    Let peek_results be list containing
    Let items_peeked be 0
    
    While items_peeked is less than count and temp_pq["size"] is greater than 0:
        Let pop_result be priority_queue_pop with pq as temp_pq
        If pop_result["success"]:
            Add dictionary with:
                value as pop_result["value"]
                priority as pop_result["priority"]
            to peek_results
            Set temp_pq to pop_result["queue"]
            Set items_peeked to items_peeked plus 1
        Otherwise:
            Break
    
    Return peek_results

Note: Utility Functions for External Use
Process called "get_current_timestamp" that returns Float:
    Let base_time be 1640995200.0
    Let random_component be simple_random with max as 1000000
    Return base_time plus random_component as Float

Process called "simple_random" that takes max as Integer returns Integer:
    Set global_random_seed to linear_congruential_generator with seed as global_random_seed
    Return global_random_seed modulo max

Process called "linear_congruential_generator" that takes seed as Integer returns Integer:
    Let a be 1664525
    Let c be 1013904223
    Let m be 4294967296
    Let next_seed be (a multiplied by seed plus c) modulo m
    Return next_seed

Let global_random_seed be 12345

Note:
This is an implementation of the MT19937 Mersenne Twister, a pseudo-random number generator.
It follows the algorithm specified by Makoto Matsumoto and Takuji Nishimura.
:End Note

Note: Define the core parameters for the MT19937 algorithm.
Define constant w as 32                           Note: Word size (in number of bits)
Define constant n as 624                           Note: Degree of recurrence
Define constant m as 397                           Note: Middle word, an offset used in the recurrence
Define constant r as 31                            Note: Separation point of one word
Define constant a as 0x9908B0DF                    Note: Coefficients of the rational normal form twist matrix

Define constant u as 11                            Note: Tempering bit shift
Define constant d as 0xFFFFFFFF                    Note: Tempering bit mask
Define constant s as 7                             Note: Tempering bit shift
Define constant b as 0x9D2C5680                    Note: Tempering bit mask
Define constant t as 15                            Note: Tempering bit shift
Define constant c as 0xEFC60000                    Note: Tempering bit mask
Define constant l as 18                            Note: Tempering bit shift

Define constant f as 1812433253                    Note: Initialization multiplier

Note: Masks to handle 32-bit arithmetic.
Define constant LOWER_MASK as (1 bitwise left shift by r) minus 1
Define constant UPPER_MASK as bitwise not LOWER_MASK

Type MersenneTwister is Dictionary with:
    mt as List[Integer]
    index as Integer

    Note: Initializes the generator from a seed value.
    Process called "initialize" that takes seed as Integer:
        Set self.index to n
        Set self.mt to a new List[Integer] of size n
        Set self.mt at index 0 to seed

        For i from 1 to n minus 1:
            Let prev_val be self.mt at index (i minus 1)
            Let temp be f multiplied by (prev_val bitwise xor (prev_val right shift by (w minus 2))) plus i
            Set self.mt at index i to temp bitwise and 0xFFFFFFFF  Note: Ensure value is 32-bit

    Note: Generates the next n values from the series. This is the core of the algorithm.
    Private Process called "twist":
        For i from 0 to n minus 1:
            Let x be (self.mt at index i bitwise and UPPER_MASK) plus (self.mt at index ((i plus 1) modulo n) bitwise and LOWER_MASK)
            Let xA be x right shift by 1

            If (x modulo 2) is not equal to 0:
                Set xA to xA bitwise xor a

            Set self.mt at index i to (self.mt at index ((i plus m) modulo n)) bitwise xor xA
        
        Set self.index to 0

    Note: Extracts a tempered pseudo-random number.
    Process called "extract_number" returns Integer:
        If self.index is greater than or equal to n:
            self.twist()

        Let y be self.mt at index self.index
        Set self.index to self.index plus 1

        Note: Apply tempering to improve the quality of the random numbers.
        Set y to y bitwise xor (y right shift by u)
        Set y to y bitwise xor ((y left shift by s) bitwise and b)
        Set y to y bitwise xor ((y left shift by t) bitwise and c)
        Set y to y bitwise xor (y right shift by l)

        Return y